Former Brazilian President  Luiz
Inacio Lula da Silva  urged Venezuelan President Hugo Chavez to
begin grooming a successor,  La Nacion  reported.  Lula, who is recovering from treatment for cancer of the
larynx, said in an interview during a visit to Argentina that
democracy is an exercise in alternating power among different
sectors of society, Buenos Aires-based La Nacion reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
